    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-15T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-15T05:00:00-05:00" n="755"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d755">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.932/10: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-15T17:00:00+07:00"
                            >April 15, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 15—5 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>663. Embassy has secret information that Chinese draft of proposed commercial and
                    consular treaty with U.S. has been completed by Foreign Office and is
                    circulating to other Ministries for examination with instructions to speed the
                        work.<note n="17" xml:id="d755fn17">For correspondence regarding the
                        proposed consular convention, see <ref target="#pg_1023">pp. 1023</ref>
                        ff.</note> It is probable that it is desired to have the draft ready for Wei
                        Tao-ming<note n="18" xml:id="d755fn18">Chinese Ambassador to the United
                        States, temporarily in China.</note> to take back to Washington when he
                    leaves in near future. I again urge that we get on with our draft of a proposed
                    treaty as rapidly as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
